HEADWORD: Hotly
<hw>Hot"ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[From <er>Hot</er>,
<pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>In a hot or fiery manner;
ardently; vehemently; violently; hastily; <as>as, a <ex>hotly</ex>
pursued</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>In a lustful manner; lustfully.</def>
<rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hot-mouthed</ent>⟦br⟧
